---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — sanzh.ar" description="Director of Engineering. Building tools, sharing everything.">

  <section style="max-width: 680px; padding: 48px 0;">
    <h1 style={`
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: 36px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin: 0 0 32px;
    `}>About</h1>

    <div style="font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;">
      <p style="margin: 0 0 24px;">
        I'm Sanzhar — a Director of Engineering from Kazakhstan. I lead teams that build products, and I still write code myself. I believe the best engineering leaders stay close to the craft.
      </p>
      <p style="margin: 0 0 24px;">
        I took a week off to kickstart this project: a personal site that doubles as a living lab for tools I actually use in my daily life. Finance tracking, tennis court booking, football team management — real apps solving real problems.
      </p>
      <p style="margin: 0 0 24px;">
        What makes this different is radical transparency. Every feature is documented with the full decision trail: the product requirements, the design process, the AI prompts I used, what they cost, and the lessons I learned. I believe showing your thinking is more valuable than showing your output.
      </p>
      <p style="margin: 0;">
        The design is inspired by the colors of the Kazakhstan flag — sky blue for openness, gold for warmth and energy. Even the color palette tells a story.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
